[SN]TITLE[SN]
PSNI Chief Constable George Hamilton 'saddened' by death of prison officer Adrian Ismay

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Northern Ireland's most senior police office has said he is saddened by the death of a prison officer days after a bomb attack in east Belfast but said he will not make assumptions about what caused his death.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
15 March 2016 Last updated at 16:40 GMT
PSNI Chief Constable George Hamilton told the BBC Adrian Ismay suffered "horrendous injuries" when the booby-trap device exploded under his van on 4 March but said police will await the results of a post-mortem before deciding if his death was due to the bomb.
